Girod - AI Voice Assistant (Arabic Version)
Overview
Girod is an AI voice assistant powered by OpenAI's ChatGPT and Python. It allows users to interact with a natural language interface, providing responses generated by the powerful ChatGPT language model. The name "Girod" is inspired by "Griott," with an Arabic twist, representing the Arab version of the assistant, tailored for the Arab Panther.

Features
Speech recognition using the SpeechRecognition library
Text-to-speech conversion using gTTS (Google Text-to-Speech) library
Integration with OpenAI's ChatGPT for generating responses
Simple and extensible design for further development
Getting Started
Prerequisites
Python installed on your machine
OpenAI API key
Required Python libraries (install using pip install -r requirements.txt)
Installation
Clone the repository:

bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/nxofares/girod-voice-assistant.git
cd girod-voice-assistant
Install dependencies:

bash
Copy code
pip install -r requirements.txt
Set up your OpenAI API key by replacing "YOUR_OPENAI_API_KEY" in the code with your actual API key.

Usage
Run the script to start interacting with Girod:

bash
Copy code
python girod_assistant.py
Girod will listen to your voice input, process it using ChatGPT, and respond accordingly.

Configuration
Adjust the settings in the script for a personalized experience. You can modify the voice used for text-to-speech, tweak the ChatGPT parameters, and more.

Contributing
Contributions are welcome! If you have ideas for improvement or new features, feel free to open an issue or submit a pull request.

